  <section class="container section-pad">
    <h2>About Electrical Service in Holland, MI</h2>
    <p>
      Holland's housing stock is a mix of historic downtown homes, mid-century neighborhoods, and newer builds along the
      lakeshore — and each calls for a different electrical approach. Older panels, knob-and-tube remnants, and aluminum
      branch wiring are common in pre-1970s homes, while newer construction tends to need EV charging, generator
      readiness, and smart-home wiring.
    </p>
    <p>
      Top Tier Electrical is based in Holland, so we know the area well — including the permit and inspection process,
      utility coordination, and the specific challenges of working in older neighborhoods near downtown vs. newer builds
      near Lake Macatawa.
    </p>

    <h3>Common Holland Projects</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Panel upgrades on older homes adding modern loads (HVAC, EV, hot tubs)</li>
      <li>EV charger installation in attached and detached garages</li>
      <li>Lighting upgrades — recessed retrofits, exterior, and decorative fixtures</li>
      <li>Code-correction work on aluminum branch circuits and ungrounded outlets</li>
      <li>Generator and transfer switch installation for Lake Michigan storm season</li>
    </ul>

